
[1]verditer

   VER'DITER, n. [verde-terre, green earth; terre-verde.]

   A preparation of copper sometimes used by painters, &c. for a blue, but
   more generally mixed with a yellow for a green color. It is a
   factitious substance of blue pigment, obtained by adding chalk or
   whiting to a solution of copper in nitric acid or aqua fortis.
